  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nSwiping left and right to change views can interfere if the user does the swipe action over an active input field.\r\n\r\n## Scenario One\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\nUsing iOS:\r\n\r\n1. Go to the flyout menu sidebar showing user profile photo and current status at top with menu items below.\r\n2. Swipe left over the users name.\r\n\r\n### Observation \r\n\r\nInstead of the flyout menu closing with the swipe gesture, the keyboard is presented to change the users name. (sidenote: I don't think a menu should be a form in the first place but demonstrates the issue well)\r\n\r\n### Expectation\r\n\r\nThe flyout menu should close.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Scenario Two\r\n\r\n### Reproduction \r\n\r\nUsing iOS:\r\n\r\n1. Go to Chats listing view.\r\n2. Press and hold an existing chat session.\r\n3. Swipe right.\r\n\r\n### Observation \r\n\r\nThere are no view panels to the left of the Chats listing view so the swipe gesture is ignored and the pressed chat session will open.\r\n\r\n### Expectation \r\n\r\nThe swipe action should be ignored and not registered as a tap.",
